main event: Two white objects were observed disappearing slowly into the dark in Pasco, Washington on 6th June 1954.
interesting points: The observation was made with instruments, indicating a scientific approach to the sighting.
The objects were observed at an elevation of approximately 30 degrees.
The duration of the observation was 2 minutes, providing a relatively extended period to study the objects.
The report mentions insufficient data, suggesting a limitation in the investigation process.
The witness, identified as Jeffrey Cowen, was a mechanic from Washingon, adding credibility to the sighting.
